The White House Office of the Vice President has released a statement regarding the services to honor the life of Beau Biden. The public is invited to attend these services. On Thursday, there will be a viewing at Legislative Hall in Dover, Delaware from 1:00 PM to 5:00 PM ET. On Friday, there will be a viewing at St. Anthony of Padua R.C. Church in Wilmington, Delaware from 1:00 PM to 4:00 PM ET and 6:00 PM to 9:00 PM ET. On Saturday at 10:30 AM ET, there will be a Mass of Christian Burial at St. Anthony of Padua R.C. Church in Wilmington, Delaware, where President Obama will deliver a eulogy. In lieu of flowers, the Biden family requests that contributions in memory of Beau Biden be made to the Beau Biden Foundation for the Protection of Children.